						<h1>Daryll Johnson</h1>
						<h5>Firefighter, EMT, Health and Fitness Coordinator/Safety</h5>
						<span class=norm>
						<strong>Age:</strong> 44<br>
						<br>
						<strong>Years on the job:</strong> 19<br>
						<br>
						<strong>What made you decide to become a Fireman?</strong><br>						
						Daryl Johnson, a Firefighter with the Chicago Fire Department remembers watching his neighbor, who was a fireman, in action.  “It was the most impressive and admirable act 
						of bravery I had ever experienced.”  It prompted Johnson to make the decision to become a firefighter.  “It’s very gratifying to offer support and encouragement in times of
						need.”  Johnson is also the health and fitness coordinator for the Chicago Fire Department.  “Being the Health and Fitness Coordinator for the Chicago Fire Department has 
						allowed me to help other members reach obtainable goals for fitness and lifestyle change.”  “I like implementing new ideas for training to sustain optimal fitness levels.”
						You can see Johnson on Channel Five News Saturday mornings doing a health and fitness segment.<br>
						<br>
						<strong>How would you like to be remembered?</strong><br>
						As a person who was dedicated to his profession, someone who was innovative, progressive and had a passion for his work.<br>
 						<br>
						<strong>We’ve all heard that Firemen are good cooks…what’s your favorite go-to meal?</strong><br>
						Grilled chicken and vegetables<br>
						<br>
						<strong>If you could live anywhere other than Chicago where would that be?</strong><br>
						The coast of Carolina<br>
 						<br>
						<strong>What’s the one thing you can always find in your refrigerator?</strong><br>
						Water<br>
						<br>
						<strong>When you’re not dressed in uniform what’s your favorite outfit to dress in?</strong><br>
						Linen wear and jeans

						
